DEATH IN RIFTS
==============

The Rifts is a dangerous world.  Death is not the end: it is a setback.

WHAT HAPPENS WHEN YOU DIE
--------------------------
When your HP (or MDC if you are an MDC being) reaches 0, you are killed.
Your killer and the room will see an appropriate death message.

You will:
  - Lose 10% of your current experience points
  - Have all worn and carried equipment placed in your corpse
  - Be transported to the grey void (the death chamber)

YOUR CORPSE
-----------
Your corpse appears in the room where you died.  All equipment you were
wearing or carrying is inside the corpse.  Other players may loot the
corpse.  After 10 minutes, the corpse dissolves and items drop to the
floor.

RESURRECTION
------------
You have two options while in the grey void:

  1. Wait: You are automatically resurrected after 2 minutes.
  2. pray : Type 'pray' to hasten resurrection to 30 seconds.

Upon resurrection you will appear at the Rift arrival zone with 1 HP
(or 1 MDC if you are an MDC being).  Your equipment remains in your
corpse.

EXPERIENCE LOSS
---------------
Each death costs you 10% of your current XP.  You do not lose levels
or stats.  This is the only penalty for dying.  Use it wisely.

PVP DEATH
---------
If you are killed by another player, the following also applies:
  - If you were good-aligned: your killer gains 50 infamy points
  - If you were evil-aligned: your killer loses 10 infamy points (hero bonus)
  - Your killer receives 50% of your XP loss as bonus experience

See also: combat, alignment, wanted, pray, score
